#. help: Channels - customTvGroupsFile
msgctxt "#30610"
msgid ""
msgstr "Only TV channels that belong to groups (i.e. have a [B]group-title[/B] attribute) will be loaded from the M3U file."

#. help: Channels - customRadioGroupsFile
msgctxt "#30611"
msgid ""
msgstr "Choose from one of the following three modes: [B]All groups[/B] Load all TV groups from the M3U file; [B]Some groups[/B] Only load the groups specified in the next options; [B]Custom groups[/B] Load a set of groups from the M3U file whose names are loaded from an XML file."

#. help: Channels - numTvGroups
msgctxt "#30612"
msgid ""
msgstr "If the previous option has been has been set to 'Some groups' you need to specify a TV group to be loaded from the M3U file. Please note that this is the group name as shown in the group-title attribute (i.e. 'UK (TV)'). This setting is case-sensitive."

#. help: Channels - numRadioGroups
msgctxt "#30614"
msgid ""
msgstr "If the previous option has been has been set to 'Some groups' you need to specify a Radio group to be fetched from the M3U file. Please not that this is the group name as shown on the group-title attribute (i.e. 'UK (Radio)'). This setting is case-sensitive."

#. help: General - radioChannelGroupsOnly
msgctxt "#30615"
msgid ""
msgstr "The file used to load the custom TV groups. The default file is `customTVGroups-example.xml`."

#. help info - EPG Settings
#. help-category: EPG Settings
msgctxt "#30616"
msgid ""
msgstr "The file used to load the custom Radio groups. The default file is `customRadioGroups-example.xml`."

#. help: EPG Settings - epgTimeShift
msgctxt "#30617"
msgid ""
msgstr "The number of TV groups to load when `Some groups` is the selected mode. Up to 5 can be chosen. If more than 5 are required the 'Custom groups' mode should be used instead."

#. help: EPG Settings - epgTSOverside
msgctxt "#30618"
msgid ""
msgstr "The number of Radio groups to load when `Some groups` is the selected mode. Up to 5 can be chosen. If more than 5 are required the 'Custom groups'  mode should be used instead."

#. help: EPG Settings - epgIgnoreCaseForChannelIds
msgctxt "#30619"
msgid ""
msgstr "Only Radio channels that belong to groups (i.e. have a [B]group-title[/B] attribute) will be loaded from the M3U file."

#. help info - Channel Logos
#. help-category: Channel Logos
msgctxt "#30620"
msgid ""
msgstr "Settings related to the EPG. Note that Kodi will only load the EPG data when it needs to. The add-on will force a load of the EPG data regardless of whether or not Kodi requests it if either catchup is enabled or XMLTV logos are required."

#. help: EPG Settings - connectionCheckIntervalSecs
msgctxt "#30625"
msgid ""
msgstr "Adjust the EPG times by this value, from -12 hours to +14 hours."

#. help-category: Channel Logos
msgctxt "#30626"
msgid ""
msgstr "Whether or not to override the time shift for all channels with `EPG time shift`. If not enabled `EPG time shift` plus the individual time shift per channel (if available) will be used."

#. help: Channel Logos - logoFromEpg
msgctxt "#30627"
msgid ""
msgstr "Ignore Case for EPG Channel IDs, also known as tvg-id's, when matching channels to EPG entries. If disabled, only case senitive matching will be used."

#. help: Genres - useEpgGenreText
msgctxt "#30628"
msgid ""
msgstr "When checking for a valid M3U file, the length of time to wait before timing out the attempt."

#. help: Genres - genresPathType
msgctxt "#30629"
msgid ""
msgstr "When checking for a valid M3U file, the length of time to wait between attempts. Note that a valid file will only be checked for on startup and once a valid file is found all checks stop."

#. help: Genres - genresPath
msgctxt "#30640"
msgid ""
msgstr "Settings related to Channel Logos."

#. help: Genres - genresUrl
msgctxt "#30644"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preference on how to handle channel logos. The options are: [B]Ignore[/B] - Don't use channel logos from an XMLTV file; [B]Prefer M3U[/B] - Use the channel logo from the M3U if available otherwise use the XMLTV logo; [B]Prefer XMLTV[/B] - Use the channel logo from the XMLTV file if available otherwise use the M3U logo."

# empty strings from id 30665 to 30679
#. help info - Advanced
#. help-category: Advanced
msgctxt "#30661"
msgid ""
msgstr "If enabled, and a genre mapping file is used to get a genre type and sub type use the EPG's genre text (i.e. 'category' text) for the genre instead of the kodi default text."

#. help: Advanced - transformMulticastStreamUrls
msgctxt "#30662"
msgid ""
msgstr "Select where to find the genres XML resource. The options are: [B]Local path[/B] - A path to a genres XML file whether it be on the device or the local network; [B]Remote path[/B] - A URL specifying the location of the genres XML file."

#. help: Advanced - udpxyHost
msgctxt "#30663"
msgid ""
msgstr "If location is [B]Local Path[/B] this setting should contain a valid path."

#. help: Advanced - udpxyPort
msgctxt "#30664"
msgid ""
msgstr "If location is [B]Remote Path[/B] this setting should contain a valid URL."

#. help: Advanced - useInputstreamAdaptiveforHls
msgctxt "#30680"
msgid ""
msgstr "Advanced settings including multicast relays, streaming properties etc."

#. help: Advanced - useFFmpegReconnect
msgctxt "#30681"
msgid ""
msgstr "Multicast (UDP/RTP) streams do not work well on Wifi networks. A multicast relay can convert the stream from UDP/RTP multicast to HTTP. Enabling this option will transform multicast stream URLs from the M3U file to HTTP addresses so they can be accesssed via a 'udpxy' relay on the local network. E.g. a UDP multicast stream URL like 'udp://@239.239.3.38:5239' would get transformed to something like 'http://192.168.1.1:4000/udp/239.239.3.38:5239'."

#. help: Advanced - defaultUserAgent
msgctxt "#30682"
msgid ""
msgstr "The hostname or ip address of the multicast relay (udpxy) on the local network."

#. help: Advanced - defaultInputstream
msgctxt "#30683"
msgid ""
msgstr "The port of the multicast relay (udpxy) on the local network."

#. help: Advanced - defaultMimeType
msgctxt "#30684"
msgid ""
msgstr "Use inputstream.adaptive instead of ffmpeg's libavformat for m3u8 (HLS) streams."

#. help: Groups - groups
msgctxt "#30685"
msgid ""
msgstr "Note this can only apply to http/https streams that are processed by libavformat (e.g. M3u8/HLS). Using libavformat can be specified in an M3U file by setting the property `inputstream` as `inputstream.ffmpeg` for kodi's internal implementation or `inputstream.ffmpegdirect` for addon version. I.e. adding the line: `#KODIPROP:inputstream=inputstream.ffmpeg`. If this option is not enabled it can still be enabled per stream/channel by adding a kodi property, i.e.: `#KODIPROP:http-reconnect=true`."

#. label-group: General - SAT>IP Auto
msgctxt "#30686"
msgid ""
msgstr "Use this User-Agent if there is not one supplied as a property or as part of the channel stream URL."

#. help: General - satipAutoConfig
msgctxt "#30687"
msgid ""
msgstr "Use this inputsream as the default if there is not one supplied as a property (KODIPROP) of the channel. Use with care as this will disable any use of the addon's default stream inspection behaviour. Note that for `inputstream.ffmpegdirect` if both `mimetype` and `inputstream.ffmpegdirect.manifest_type` are unset stream inspection will still occur if required."

#. label: General - satipServerHost
msgctxt "#30688"
msgid ""
msgstr "Use this MIME type as the default if there is not one supplied as a property (KODIPROP) of the channel. Use with care as this will disable any use of the addon's default stream inspection behaviour."

#. help: General - satipServerHost
